 system 
 
 1. Introduction 
 
 Credit is important for development. It capitalises 
 farmers and businesspersons to begin/try new investments or put into use new technologies. It helps smooth 
 consumption by providing working capital and reduces poorness in the process. Both formal and informal 
 lenders are active in (away from cities) credit market (Adams and 
 * Corresponding author. 
