 The skewed distribution of formal credit may have 
 an hit/effect on farming-based growth and (away from cities) poorness in 
 Pakistan. Since the working well of small householders is higher than that of large holders according to 
 established development books, the hit/effect of formal credit is expected to be higher for smallholders 
 than for large holders. Since the large holders receive 
 the majority of formal credit, one can guesse that the skewed distribution of formal credit 
 has a limiting effect on (away from cities) growth and welfare. 
 This is in fact a concern, even when only one-third 
 of (away from cities) borrowing in volume comes from formal 
 sources. 
 
 4. Credit impact test: an econometric 
 (solid basic structure on which bigger things can be built) 
 The purpose here is to guess the hits/effects of formal/institutional credit on (away from cities) welfare. Since formal/institutional part/area in Pakistan is ruled by 
 the ADBP, this amounts to guessing the hit/effect of 
 ADBP loans on (away from cities) household welfare. What (people who work to find information) watch/notice is the amount of credit received from 
 ADBP that is based on both the demand for and the 
 supply of credit. The real difficulty is how to untangle the demand from the supply. Often household 
 and area (features/ qualities/ traits) decide/figure out the household's demand for credit. But these same (features/ qualities/ traits) also 
 influence the supply of credit, giving rise to a problem of selection bias. It is possible that borrowers are 
 more productive not because of the loan, but because 
 they are more creative, and hard-working. It 
 is also possible that borrowers are productive and, 
 hence, able to pay back, not because they have better ability but because operate in a more productive (surrounding conditions). 
 Lenders such as the ADBP screen borrowers based 
 on their qualities and (related to surrounding conditions or the health of the Earth) (features/ qualities/ traits) which 
 are not easily watched/followed by (people who work to find information). So, the al- 
 
 location of ADBP credit is not random. 10 As money 
 are fixed, the lenders would like to set apart money 
 to the best possible borrowers and in the best possible agroclimate area. We used a competitors' model 
 (solid basic structure on which bigger things can be built) for the decision making process of ADBP 
 lending. 
