 rupee of borrowing from a formal source, such as 
 the ADBP, on household results such as consumption, allowing the household to (change to make better/change to fit new conditions) its borrowing 
 'portfolio' and all other behaviours, in response. 12 
 Although the maximum chance guess (MLE) is 
 better since it yields (producing a lot with very little waste) guesses, running MLE 
 is a awkward process compared to the two-stage 
 method which provides consistent guesses. Because of this, 
 we use a two-stage method to guess the hit/effect of 
 credit. 
 
