 7. Cost-effectiveness of the ADBP 
 If the helping payment dependence of the ADBP cannot be 
 fully avoided, can it be reasonable in terms of the social 
 benefits that it creates? We have discovered that 
 the ADBP is not a (producing a lot for a given amount of money) delivery system as 
 it depends on payments. (even though there is the existence of) the high loan default 
 costs and helping payment dependence, it is important to find 
 out whether it is (producing a lot with very little waste) from the point of view of the 
 social goal to deliver targeted credit. Since the 
 delivery of farm credit clearly shows/includes government policies, 
 it is worth exploring whether it is (producing a lot for a given amount of money) to<p><strong>NOTE: This document is incomplete. It was shortened to the maximum document length of 50,000 characters.</strong></p><div style="clear:both">&nbsp;</div>
